By NONSINDISO QWABE and SIKHO NTSHOBANE East London police arrested a 45-year-old man on Saturday after he was found in possession of drugs worth about R2-million at his Sohco flat in Amalinda.  The man is in police custody, where he will remain until his expected appearance before the East London Magistrate’s Court tomorrow. Nkosana Dlala, 31, is said to have last been seen by his boss on Friday at 6am when he gave Dlala a vehicle in which to transport people around East London. Police said a young Willowvale girl had been raped on Saturday while sleeping in her home in Upper Gwadu village. A man, 54, was shot and killed in Ngoma village in Willowvale on Saturday. Police arrested a 28-year-old man in Tsolo following the fatal stabbing of a another man in Tsolo on Saturday night. Police are investigating murder after a 29-year-old man was found dead in Ngangelizwe Township in Mthatha. — sikhon@dispatch.co.za; nonsindisoq@dispatch.co.za